WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.353 --> 00:00:04.614
<i>SCOFIELD: Previously
on</i> Prison Break.

2
00:00:04.638 --> 00:00:06.516
There's something
about this guy.

3
00:00:06.540 --> 00:00:08.818
It's like he knows where
we're going. what we're thinking.

4
00:00:08.842 --> 00:00:10.320
<i>If that's true. it's
just a matter of time</i>

5
00:00:10.344 --> 00:00:12.171
<i>before he finds out
about the money in Utah.</i>

6
00:00:12.195 --> 00:00:14.362
our way into Mexico.

7
00:00:14.431 --> 00:00:15.864
Everything.

8
00:00:21.638 --> 00:00:24.467
You can have an attorney present
during questioning. now or in the future.

9
00:00:24.491 --> 00:00:25.974
Caroline. they're taking her in.

10
00:00:26.060 --> 00:00:27.760
Of course. I'll
keep an eye on her.

11
00:00:27.812 --> 00:00:29.344
I did it. Dad.

12
00:00:29.430 --> 00:00:31.163
Just do as you're told.

13
00:00:31.232 --> 00:00:34.833
Otherwise there will be
consequences that will affect us all.

14
00:00:34.901 --> 00:00:36.918
My dad's an Air Force colonel.

15
00:00:36.987 --> 00:00:39.204
When I told him I
was staying in a hotel

16
00:00:39.272 --> 00:00:42.424
with a guy that I
maybe sort of liked.

17
00:00:43.444 --> 00:00:45.560
he lost it.

18
00:00:45.629 --> 00:00:47.306
What are you doing
here? Where's Maricruz?

19
00:00:47.330 --> 00:00:48.664
She's with me now.

20
00:00:48.732 --> 00:00:49.892
Just tell me where she is.

21
00:00:49.916 --> 00:00:51.750
Hey. Fernando. Slow down. man.

22
00:00:51.802 --> 00:00:54.269
I was trying to tell you.
the wedding is in Vegas.

23
00:00:56.790 --> 00:00:58.056
So which one of them was it?

24
00:00:58.125 --> 00:00:59.774
Might be Scofield.

25
00:00:59.844 --> 00:01:02.744
Probably gonna find
his brother in there. too.

26
00:01:02.813 --> 00:01:05.533
<i>AUTOMATED VOICE:
Where to. sir?</i> Utah.

27
00:01:13.874 --> 00:01:15.918
<i>WOMAN ON RADIO: This
morning. authorities in Illinois</i>

28
00:01:15.942 --> 00:01:17.721
<i>issued an update on
the escaped convicts</i>

29
00:01:17.745 --> 00:01:20.612
<i>known until now as
the Fox River Eight.</i>

30
00:01:20.681 --> 00:01:23.192
<i>Chicago mob boss. John
Abruzzi. was gunned down</i>

31
00:01:23.216 --> 00:01:25.584
<i>outside a Washington
D.C. motel last night</i>

32
00:01:25.653 --> 00:01:28.904
<i>after investigators received
a tip from an informant.</i>

33
00:01:28.972 --> 00:01:33.441
<i>The other seven escapees are still
at large and considered dangerous.</i>

34
00:01:33.510 --> 00:01:35.109
<i>A Florida man wanted in...</i>

35
00:01:35.179 --> 00:01:37.212
(RADIO TURNS OFF)

36
00:01:37.280 --> 00:01:40.076
I didn't think Abruzzi
would be the first to eat it.

37
00:01:40.100 --> 00:01:43.235
I have a feeling we're
in for lots of surprises.

38
00:01:43.303 --> 00:01:44.747
They said seven
are still out there.

39
00:01:44.771 --> 00:01:46.832
So much for faking our deaths.

40
00:01:46.856 --> 00:01:49.708
I bought us some
time. that's what counts.

41
00:01:52.362 --> 00:01:53.678
How much further?

42
00:01:53.747 --> 00:01:54.996
Seventy. 80 miles.

43
00:01:55.065 --> 00:01:56.398
Good. Means we should be hitting

44
00:01:56.467 --> 00:01:58.016
the Double K Ranch
by this afternoon.

45
00:01:58.085 --> 00:02:00.112
Or we can keep driving.
pick up LJ and hit Panama.

46
00:02:00.136 --> 00:02:02.470
We can't hit Panama!
We can't hit anything!

47
00:02:02.539 --> 00:02:04.523
We can't do anything
without the money.

48
00:02:04.592 --> 00:02:07.075
We need to find Charles' stash.

49
00:02:09.062 --> 00:02:11.997
I know some other guys who
are thinking the same thing.

50
00:02:13.951 --> 00:02:18.203
The money is buried under a silo

51
00:02:18.271 --> 00:02:22.791
at the Double K Ranch
just outside of Tooele. Utah.

52
00:02:22.859 --> 00:02:25.210
There's $5 million there.

53
00:02:30.233 --> 00:02:31.733
<i>(TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWING)</i>

54
00:02:41.011 --> 00:02:42.277
TICKET CHECKER: Tickets?

55
00:02:43.130 --> 00:02:44.146
(CLEARS THROAT)

56
00:02:44.214 --> 00:02:46.048
You know. when I
was in Cheyenne.

57
00:02:46.116 --> 00:02:48.300
I pulled my ticket
out of the bag.

58
00:02:48.369 --> 00:02:50.785
(CHUCKLES) it tore in
half. and I have no idea

59
00:02:50.854 --> 00:02:52.837
what happened to the other part.

60
00:02:52.906 --> 00:02:54.333
They didn't issue
you a replacement?

61
00:02:54.357 --> 00:02:57.242
No. The young lady. I
think her name was Sherry.

62
00:02:57.294 --> 00:02:59.427
she actually said
that this half is okay

63
00:02:59.496 --> 00:03:00.895
because the bar code is on it.

64
00:03:00.964 --> 00:03:03.109
Well. you really
need the whole ticket.

65
00:03:03.133 --> 00:03:05.634
This is exactly what
I was trying to avoid.

66
00:03:05.702 --> 00:03:08.086
She said that everything
would be fine because...

67
00:03:08.154 --> 00:03:10.250
That's okay. It'll do for now.

68
00:03:10.274 --> 00:03:12.902
But make sure you ask for a
replacement when you get to Provo.

69
00:03:12.926 --> 00:03:15.110
I definitely will. Thank you.

70
00:03:16.146 --> 00:03:17.645
It's always something. huh?

71
00:03:17.714 --> 00:03:19.181
Oh. God. I know.

72
00:03:25.072 --> 00:03:27.072
<i>(SOFT MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

73
00:03:30.827 --> 00:03:32.460
DEBRA: I don't want to go home.

74
00:03:35.031 --> 00:03:36.831
I wish we could keep driving.

75
00:03:36.900 --> 00:03:39.340
I don't think your pops
will be down for that.

76
00:03:40.537 --> 00:03:42.303
Wouldn't it be fun?

77
00:03:43.524 --> 00:03:47.142
We could go to Hawaii.

78
00:03:47.211 --> 00:03:49.344
You can't drive to Hawaii.

79
00:03:49.412 --> 00:03:51.513
Yo. I know.

80
00:03:52.282 --> 00:03:54.416
I'm just saying I wish.

81
00:03:54.484 --> 00:03:56.167
(KNOCKING AT DOOR)

82
00:03:57.404 --> 00:03:58.737
Oh. uh...

83
00:03:58.805 --> 00:04:00.454
No. Don't get it. They'll leave.

84
00:04:00.523 --> 00:04:02.123
Just let me see who it is.

85
00:04:08.098 --> 00:04:09.881
It's a cop.

86
00:04:09.950 --> 00:04:11.870
No. no. no. no. no.
Whoa. whoa. whoa.

87
00:04:15.122 --> 00:04:16.471
Sorry to disturb you. ma'am.

88
00:04:16.539 --> 00:04:18.459
Have you happened
to see this person?

89
00:04:55.579 --> 00:04:57.019
Last night we got
a few phone calls

90
00:04:57.080 --> 00:04:58.963
that he was spotted in the area.

91
00:04:59.032 --> 00:05:00.599
So we're going door-to-door.

92
00:05:01.752 --> 00:05:03.313
Why are you looking for him?

93
00:05:03.337 --> 00:05:06.087
He escaped from prison in
Illinois a couple of days ago.

94
00:05:06.155 --> 00:05:07.839
Have you seen him?

95
00:05:12.713 --> 00:05:15.696
No. He doesn't look familiar.

96
00:05:16.566 --> 00:05:18.032
Are you sure?

97
00:05:19.436 --> 00:05:21.002
Yeah. I'm sure.

98
00:05:23.607 --> 00:05:25.940
All right. Thanks for your time.

99
00:05:32.149 --> 00:05:33.782
Whoa. Whoa. whoa. whoa.

100
00:05:33.851 --> 00:05:34.961
This ain't...

101
00:05:34.985 --> 00:05:37.368
This is not what
you think. all right?

102
00:05:37.437 --> 00:05:39.520
Look. Trust me.

103
00:05:39.589 --> 00:05:41.857
Listen. Just listen.

104
00:05:41.925 --> 00:05:43.308
Okay?

105
00:05:43.377 --> 00:05:46.895
All I did was steal
a baseball card.

106
00:05:46.964 --> 00:05:50.404
Okay? I'm not like those
other fools up in there.

107
00:05:51.735 --> 00:05:55.103
I'm gonna go for a walk. okay?

108
00:05:55.171 --> 00:05:58.089
Just... I'm gonna leave
my keys right here.

109
00:05:58.158 --> 00:06:02.610
And when I come back.
my car will be gone.

110
00:06:02.679 --> 00:06:06.864
I'm sure. in a few hours.
they'll find it somewhere.

111
00:06:08.201 --> 00:06:09.517
abandoned.

112
00:06:14.508 --> 00:06:16.024
Wait. Wait.

113
00:06:22.499 --> 00:06:24.716
I wish it could be different.

114
00:06:26.453 --> 00:06:27.869
I have to go.

115
00:06:47.741 --> 00:06:48.906
Tooele.

116
00:06:48.975 --> 00:06:50.908
SCOFIELD: I
think it's To-ill-uh.

117
00:06:50.977 --> 00:06:52.660
Hell of a town.

118
00:06:52.729 --> 00:06:54.012
Small is good.

119
00:06:54.081 --> 00:06:55.697
Means the ranch
will be easier to find.

120
00:06:55.766 --> 00:06:58.033
All we got to do
is get that money

121
00:06:58.101 --> 00:07:00.318
and we'll be out
of here by nightfall.

122
00:07:00.387 --> 00:07:01.619
Nice.

123
00:07:22.526 --> 00:07:25.277
Oh. sir. Soil test came
back from Scofield's crash.

124
00:07:25.345 --> 00:07:26.739
Not that you need
any more proof.

125
00:07:26.763 --> 00:07:29.747
but he really went
out of his way this time.

126
00:07:29.816 --> 00:07:31.232
What else do you have?

127
00:07:31.301 --> 00:07:33.418
Man was violently
assaulted in Nebraska

128
00:07:33.487 --> 00:07:35.503
by a hitchhiker matching
Bagwell's description.

129
00:07:35.572 --> 00:07:37.322
who's headed west on the I-80.

130
00:07:37.390 --> 00:07:39.273
Omaha's putting
together a photo lineup.

131
00:07:39.342 --> 00:07:41.476
What do you have on Scofield?

132
00:07:41.544 --> 00:07:45.379
What does anybody
have on Scofield?

133
00:07:45.448 --> 00:07:48.383
PERTZ: I've got some
results from his hard drive.

134
00:07:48.452 --> 00:07:51.352
the one recovered
from the river.

135
00:07:51.421 --> 00:07:54.300
We were able to use the sector
editor to restore the master boot.

136
00:07:54.324 --> 00:07:56.235
So from that... I don't
care how you did it.

137
00:07:56.259 --> 00:07:57.892
What do you have?

138
00:07:59.796 --> 00:08:03.164
More than half the contents
of the buffer. about 60%.

139
00:08:09.255 --> 00:08:10.366
It looks pretty random.

140
00:08:10.390 --> 00:08:11.406
Print it up. All of it.

141
00:08:11.475 --> 00:08:13.274
I want it on my desk.

142
00:08:16.646 --> 00:08:18.946
Well. guess what?

143
00:08:19.015 --> 00:08:22.016
No listing for a Double K Ranch.

144
00:08:22.085 --> 00:08:25.103
Excuse me. You know where
I might find Double K Ranch?

145
00:08:25.172 --> 00:08:26.354
What you call it?

146
00:08:26.422 --> 00:08:27.789
Double K Ranch.

147
00:08:27.857 --> 00:08:28.940
No.

148
00:08:29.009 --> 00:08:30.475
You from around here?

149
00:08:30.544 --> 00:08:33.227
Yeah. Born and raised.
There's no Double nothing.

150
00:08:33.297 --> 00:08:34.813
Great. Thank you.

151
00:08:37.016 --> 00:08:39.178
LINCOLN: Looks like
Westmoreland spent his last breath

152
00:08:39.202 --> 00:08:40.585
blowing smoke up your ass.

153
00:08:40.654 --> 00:08:42.331
There's one way to find out.

154
00:08:42.355 --> 00:08:44.784
The county keeps
property records.

155
00:08:44.808 --> 00:08:47.241
Every plot is mapped
out with dimensions.

156
00:08:47.310 --> 00:08:48.743
It's public record.

157
00:08:48.812 --> 00:08:51.879
But if there is a tax
assessor's office here.

158
00:08:52.749 --> 00:08:54.616
it's gonna be in there.

159
00:08:54.684 --> 00:08:56.734
In the municipal building.

160
00:08:57.971 --> 00:09:00.188
Lot of cops in there. Michael.

161
00:09:03.426 --> 00:09:04.458
<i>(PHONE RINGING)</i>

162
00:09:04.527 --> 00:09:06.978
<i>MAN: Dispatch. DEBRA: Someone...</i>

163
00:09:07.046 --> 00:09:08.958
<i>Someone stole
my car this morning.</i>

164
00:09:08.982 --> 00:09:11.277
<i>I'm at the Lotus
Motel off Interstate 80.</i>

165
00:09:11.301 --> 00:09:13.462
<i>Did you see who took it? No.</i>

166
00:09:13.486 --> 00:09:16.766
<i>I went out for a walk. and
when I came back. it was gone.</i>

167
00:09:16.806 --> 00:09:18.840
<i>This morning? Why
didn't you call before?</i>

168
00:09:18.908 --> 00:09:20.942
<i>I... I don't know.</i>

169
00:10:19.001 --> 00:10:21.269
Mr. Kellerman. Mr. Kim.

170
00:10:23.173 --> 00:10:25.673
Surprised to see you in Chicago.

171
00:10:25.741 --> 00:10:27.091
Just looking for updates.

172
00:10:27.160 --> 00:10:29.560
Sara Tancredi. I'm on it.

173
00:10:29.629 --> 00:10:31.273
Is pursuing her the
best use of your time?

174
00:10:31.297 --> 00:10:32.613
It is.

175
00:10:32.682 --> 00:10:34.293
She's in contact with Scofield.

176
00:10:34.317 --> 00:10:36.400
I was there when
he called yesterday.

177
00:10:36.469 --> 00:10:38.589
We stay with her. she
takes us right to him.

178
00:10:38.638 --> 00:10:40.521
he takes us to Burrows.

179
00:10:41.358 --> 00:10:43.091
All right.

180
00:10:43.159 --> 00:10:44.325
If you're that confident.

181
00:10:44.394 --> 00:10:45.510
I am.

182
00:10:46.913 --> 00:10:48.213
I'll let the President know.

183
00:10:48.281 --> 00:10:50.097
I contact the
President directly.

184
00:10:52.068 --> 00:10:53.718
I'll contact her.

185
00:10:55.021 --> 00:10:56.571
Keep me posted.

186
00:11:22.999 --> 00:11:26.734
<i>GROUP LEADER: If you want to
restore dignity. you need to take action.</i>

187
00:11:26.803 --> 00:11:30.621
<i>Making amends requires
much more than saying I'm sorry.</i>

188
00:11:30.690 --> 00:11:33.024
It means learning to change.

189
00:11:33.093 --> 00:11:35.276
The apology is
just the first step.

190
00:11:35.345 --> 00:11:42.283
The most important thing is that you
display honesty. courage and compassion

191
00:11:42.369 --> 00:11:44.235
when you extend your apologies.

192
00:11:44.303 --> 00:11:47.672
You need to earn
your forgiveness.

193
00:11:47.741 --> 00:11:49.974
We'll talk about
it more on Friday.

194
00:12:03.890 --> 00:12:05.623
I got a great idea.

195
00:12:05.691 --> 00:12:07.625
What's that?

196
00:12:07.694 --> 00:12:10.945
Since you are such a fan of
lame. store-bought blueberry pie.

197
00:12:11.014 --> 00:12:14.916
I am going to bake you a
real pie of your choice tonight.

198
00:12:18.488 --> 00:12:20.472
I can't.

199
00:12:20.540 --> 00:12:24.100
I really don't need to be seeing
anyone right now who isn't my therapist.

200
00:12:26.463 --> 00:12:29.447
I've been a hermit lately. too.

201
00:12:29.516 --> 00:12:31.160
My partner. Daniel.
is away on business.

202
00:12:31.184 --> 00:12:34.402
I've been sitting around
every night by myself.

203
00:12:34.470 --> 00:12:36.103
Kind of pathetic.

204
00:12:37.440 --> 00:12:40.091
I am so sorry. I
thought you meant...

205
00:12:40.876 --> 00:12:42.210
Um...

206
00:12:42.295 --> 00:12:43.644
I thought...

207
00:12:44.530 --> 00:12:45.880
The pie...

208
00:12:45.948 --> 00:12:47.848
Oh. no.

209
00:12:47.917 --> 00:12:49.384
(KELLERMAN LAUGHS)

210
00:12:49.452 --> 00:12:51.713
That's my ego. No. I
was really talking about...

211
00:12:51.737 --> 00:12:53.466
Pie? Yeah. actual blueberries.

212
00:12:53.490 --> 00:12:56.068
Like. we'd make pie and
watch <i>Fried Green Tomatoes.</i>

213
00:12:56.092 --> 00:12:57.425
I get it. I get it.

214
00:12:57.494 --> 00:12:59.527
I'm the best ex-junkie
cook in this town.

215
00:12:59.596 --> 00:13:02.263
Thank you. I just... I got
to clean my apartment.

216
00:13:02.332 --> 00:13:03.547
It's disgusting.

217
00:13:03.616 --> 00:13:05.628
and I realize that sounds
like an excuse. It's not.

218
00:13:05.652 --> 00:13:07.168
No. no. no. I get it.

219
00:13:08.188 --> 00:13:10.204
You do what you got to do.

220
00:13:11.307 --> 00:13:12.790
Have a good night.

221
00:13:14.577 --> 00:13:16.077
You deliver?

222
00:13:25.605 --> 00:13:26.971
Next batch.

223
00:13:34.630 --> 00:13:35.630
Ow.

224
00:13:57.053 --> 00:13:59.070
Just put it on the desk.

225
00:14:01.641 --> 00:14:03.051
Does any of this
stuff mean anything?

226
00:14:03.075 --> 00:14:04.608
I don't know. Ask me later.

227
00:14:04.677 --> 00:14:06.193
Think he's a genius
or a whack job?

228
00:14:06.262 --> 00:14:07.522
I think we answered
that question

229
00:14:07.546 --> 00:14:09.358
when we assigned
100 agents to the case.

230
00:14:09.382 --> 00:14:10.943
So why don't you go and
get me the rest of it. huh?

231
00:14:10.967 --> 00:14:12.884
Does that work for you?

232
00:14:45.134 --> 00:14:47.468
Well. lackaday!

233
00:14:47.537 --> 00:14:50.037
I just found me an in-betweener.

234
00:14:51.925 --> 00:14:53.486
Where's you going
in such a hurry. huh?

235
00:14:53.510 --> 00:14:55.042
None of your beeswax. yo.

236
00:14:55.111 --> 00:14:56.760
I knows where.

237
00:14:56.829 --> 00:14:59.897
Same place as every other man
that was in that room that night.

238
00:14:59.966 --> 00:15:01.432
They all coming around here

239
00:15:01.501 --> 00:15:04.619
for a big family reunion
at the Ku Klux Ranch.

240
00:15:04.688 --> 00:15:06.904
If they ain't here already.

241
00:15:06.973 --> 00:15:08.834
Look. there ain't no
country fool in this town

242
00:15:08.858 --> 00:15:10.469
ever heard of the
Double K Ranch.

243
00:15:10.493 --> 00:15:12.904
Seems like you've been misinformed.
Indeedy there is a Double K.

244
00:15:12.928 --> 00:15:14.940
It's just a matter of who
gets there first. all right?

245
00:15:14.964 --> 00:15:17.348
The stars are gonna
collide in Tooele. my friend.

246
00:15:17.416 --> 00:15:19.701
You're gonna need
me on your side.

247
00:15:19.786 --> 00:15:21.496
This ain't Fox River. all right?

248
00:15:21.520 --> 00:15:23.103
I don't need any of you.

249
00:15:25.007 --> 00:15:29.294
As you can see. I need you.

250
00:15:30.847 --> 00:15:34.148
Get your grubby
paws off me. you freak.

251
00:15:34.217 --> 00:15:36.733
I ain't your ditch
digger no more.

252
00:15:36.802 --> 00:15:38.603
I don't need nothing from you.

253
00:15:38.671 --> 00:15:40.388
I don't need nothing.

254
00:15:40.473 --> 00:15:42.557
You might.

255
00:15:42.625 --> 00:15:45.860
If a man knew where he
was supposed to be looking.

256
00:16:00.175 --> 00:16:01.326
<i>SUCRE: Hi. hi.</i>

257
00:16:01.394 --> 00:16:03.277
Are you having the Hector Avila

258
00:16:03.346 --> 00:16:05.179
and Maricruz Delgado
wedding today?

259
00:16:05.949 --> 00:16:07.365
Avila.

260
00:16:07.433 --> 00:16:09.384
No? Okay. thanks.

261
00:16:16.142 --> 00:16:18.475
Hi. Are you having
the Hector Avila

262
00:16:18.544 --> 00:16:20.704
and Maricruz Delgado
wedding today?

263
00:16:21.997 --> 00:16:23.181
Avila.

264
00:16:24.501 --> 00:16:25.767
Delgado.

265
00:16:26.369 --> 00:16:27.602
Really?

266
00:16:28.671 --> 00:16:29.804
When?

267
00:16:40.983 --> 00:16:43.734
Stay calm. We'll be out
of here in 10 minutes.

268
00:16:45.138 --> 00:16:46.871
One at a time.

269
00:16:46.939 --> 00:16:48.539
Clear.

270
00:16:48.607 --> 00:16:49.847
Back up.

271
00:16:53.646 --> 00:16:55.262
You wearing a watch?

272
00:16:56.365 --> 00:16:57.715
Yeah.

273
00:17:09.829 --> 00:17:11.112
Nice day.

274
00:17:13.599 --> 00:17:14.815
Thanks.

275
00:17:24.160 --> 00:17:26.044
This is exactly what we need.

276
00:17:26.112 --> 00:17:29.129
It's a map of every
parcel of land.

277
00:17:29.198 --> 00:17:32.132
Topography.
buildings. everything.

278
00:17:36.438 --> 00:17:38.306
Karl Kokosing. Double K.

279
00:17:38.374 --> 00:17:40.774
I don't like the way
this guy is looking at us.

280
00:17:50.336 --> 00:17:51.935
1213.

281
00:17:54.791 --> 00:17:56.307
Where's 1213?

282
00:18:03.032 --> 00:18:05.349
CLERK: Miss Sebern. I
need to speak with you.

283
00:18:05.417 --> 00:18:07.819
Come on. man.
we got to roll now.

284
00:18:09.122 --> 00:18:10.638
Miss Sebern.

285
00:18:10.706 --> 00:18:12.757
Come on. You got the map?

286
00:18:16.512 --> 00:18:17.594
No.

287
00:18:19.215 --> 00:18:20.881
Someone else does.

288
00:18:30.276 --> 00:18:31.642
Someone got here before us.

289
00:18:31.694 --> 00:18:33.277
It's the only explanation.

290
00:18:39.334 --> 00:18:41.774
Son of a bitch is still alive.

291
00:18:43.957 --> 00:18:45.138
Hey. pretty!

292
00:18:45.207 --> 00:18:46.357
What the...

293
00:18:47.309 --> 00:18:49.677
What you gonna do. scream?

294
00:18:51.114 --> 00:18:53.731
How the hell are
you still breathing?

295
00:18:53.800 --> 00:18:56.316
What the hell did
you do to your hand?

296
00:18:56.385 --> 00:18:57.968
(EXCLAIMS IN PAIN)

297
00:18:58.037 --> 00:18:59.937
Easy. easy.

298
00:19:00.006 --> 00:19:02.322
I recently had some work done.

299
00:19:02.391 --> 00:19:04.275
Where is the map?

300
00:19:04.343 --> 00:19:06.810
Easy. Easy. Easy.

301
00:19:06.879 --> 00:19:08.212
I don't have it.

302
00:19:08.281 --> 00:19:09.564
SCOFIELD: Well. where is it?

303
00:19:09.632 --> 00:19:11.615
I'm telling you.
I don't have it.

304
00:19:11.684 --> 00:19:13.366
I don't have it. all right?

305
00:19:13.435 --> 00:19:15.069
You were there. We saw you.

306
00:19:15.138 --> 00:19:16.887
It was gone when I got there.

307
00:19:16.956 --> 00:19:18.734
Now. why don't you keep
your pooch away from me?

308
00:19:18.758 --> 00:19:20.624
I'll tell you everything I know.

309
00:19:23.629 --> 00:19:25.896
It's the kid. He has it.

310
00:19:25.948 --> 00:19:29.150
I saw him this morning
and I needed some help.

311
00:19:29.218 --> 00:19:31.135
We made a deal. all right?

312
00:19:31.204 --> 00:19:32.570
He said that he would dig.

313
00:19:32.639 --> 00:19:34.588
I told him where
we could get a map.

314
00:19:35.325 --> 00:19:36.590
What kid?

315
00:19:38.561 --> 00:19:39.910
What kid?

316
00:19:53.309 --> 00:19:55.576
BENNETT: The best
thing to do is nothing.

317
00:19:55.644 --> 00:19:57.156
That's how I'm going
to get the US Senate

318
00:19:57.180 --> 00:19:59.190
to confirm my vice
presidency? Do nothing?

319
00:19:59.214 --> 00:20:00.709
Shows them you can do the job.

320
00:20:00.733 --> 00:20:01.933
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

321
00:20:01.985 --> 00:20:03.217
Wait a minute.

322
00:20:03.853 --> 00:20:06.253
It's my daughter.

323
00:20:06.322 --> 00:20:08.856
Sir. we need to talk
about your daughter.

324
00:20:08.925 --> 00:20:10.341
What about her?

325
00:20:10.410 --> 00:20:13.327
Well. the media is all over
this Fox River situation.

326
00:20:13.396 --> 00:20:16.530
We think it would be best if you
could distance yourself from her.

327
00:20:16.599 --> 00:20:18.209
If I hear this one more time...

328
00:20:18.233 --> 00:20:20.066
I paid her bail. I walked away.

329
00:20:20.920 --> 00:20:22.886
I have distanced myself.

330
00:20:26.158 --> 00:20:27.825
Give me a minute.

331
00:20:31.114 --> 00:20:33.096
Hey. Dad. it's me.

332
00:20:33.165 --> 00:20:34.598
When you get a chance.

333
00:20:34.667 --> 00:20:36.747
I really need to talk to
you about some things.

334
00:20:38.137 --> 00:20:40.337
Actually a lot of things.

335
00:20:40.406 --> 00:20:45.075
The most important one is
that I owe you an apology.

336
00:20:45.144 --> 00:20:49.080
I realize that I've made
things difficult for you lately.

337
00:20:50.049 --> 00:20:51.082
Um...

338
00:20:51.150 --> 00:20:53.017
(DOORBELL RINGS)

339
00:20:53.085 --> 00:20:56.219
And I want to take
responsibility for that.

340
00:20:58.474 --> 00:20:59.990
Call me back. Bye.

341
00:21:02.045 --> 00:21:04.545
Hi. I know I'm early.
but I brought dinner.

342
00:21:04.613 --> 00:21:05.813
Come on in.

343
00:21:05.882 --> 00:21:07.893
You're not a
vegetarian. are you? No.

344
00:21:07.917 --> 00:21:09.867
Just shut that behind you.

345
00:21:21.397 --> 00:21:22.724
Do you mind if I
check my e-mail?

346
00:21:22.748 --> 00:21:23.975
Not at all. Here.

347
00:21:23.999 --> 00:21:25.316
Oh. you're so kind. Thank you.

348
00:21:25.385 --> 00:21:26.625
Absolutely.

349
00:21:49.708 --> 00:21:51.670
Do you happen to
have a pen handy?

350
00:21:51.694 --> 00:21:52.909
Yeah.

351
00:21:52.979 --> 00:21:54.039
Thank you so much.

352
00:21:54.063 --> 00:21:55.303
I'm so sorry to bother you.

353
00:21:55.381 --> 00:21:57.743
Not at all. Look. I have
a little pencil and a pad.

354
00:21:57.767 --> 00:21:59.099
Thank you.

355
00:22:06.192 --> 00:22:07.892
Sir? Sir?

356
00:22:07.960 --> 00:22:08.993
Yeah.

357
00:22:09.061 --> 00:22:11.095
No Sherry in Cheyenne.

358
00:22:11.163 --> 00:22:12.824
Your ticket is not
valid for travel.

359
00:22:12.848 --> 00:22:14.064
Oh. well. hold on. now.

360
00:22:14.133 --> 00:22:16.383
That can't be right.
That can't be right.

361
00:22:16.452 --> 00:22:18.412
Excuse me for a second. Sure.

362
00:22:20.272 --> 00:22:21.583
All right now. listen. brother.

363
00:22:21.607 --> 00:22:23.841
I'm gonna give it
to you straight up.

364
00:22:23.909 --> 00:22:25.887
Now. seriously. I'm broke. okay?

365
00:22:25.911 --> 00:22:27.945
That's the truth.

366
00:22:28.013 --> 00:22:32.399
I just ran into some
trouble a while back and...

367
00:22:32.468 --> 00:22:34.379
I'm just really trying to
pull it all together now.

368
00:22:34.403 --> 00:22:36.019
You understand?

369
00:22:36.088 --> 00:22:38.616
Well. you can tell that to the
authorities in about five minutes.

370
00:22:38.640 --> 00:22:41.253
Oh. come on. brother. We don't
have to get the authorities involved.

371
00:22:41.277 --> 00:22:42.893
No. it's too late.

372
00:22:42.961 --> 00:22:44.945
They're already
waiting at the next stop.

373
00:22:45.014 --> 00:22:48.548
These guys here. they're
gonna sit with you until we stop.

374
00:22:50.236 --> 00:22:52.919
I understand. I understand.

375
00:23:00.028 --> 00:23:01.361
Hey!

376
00:23:01.430 --> 00:23:03.196
Come here. Sir.

377
00:23:03.265 --> 00:23:05.115
Hey. you can't go in there!

378
00:23:26.088 --> 00:23:28.739
Okay. we've got a
confirmed sighting on Franklin.

379
00:23:28.808 --> 00:23:31.658
Jumped out of a moving
train in Preston. Idaho.

380
00:23:31.727 --> 00:23:35.078
What is a black man from
Chicago doing in Idaho?

381
00:23:35.147 --> 00:23:36.497
He's got to be lost.

382
00:23:36.566 --> 00:23:38.949
Franklin's in Preston.
Idaho. Bagwell's in Nebraska.

383
00:23:39.018 --> 00:23:41.268
And both men have never
been across the Mississippi.

384
00:23:41.337 --> 00:23:43.687
Visiting friends and
family? I don't think so.

385
00:23:43.756 --> 00:23:46.373
And not south of the border.

386
00:23:46.459 --> 00:23:50.594
They're due west. and
we need to know why.

387
00:23:53.815 --> 00:23:54.898
LINCOLN: Out.

388
00:23:57.136 --> 00:23:58.263
What's going on. friends?

389
00:23:58.287 --> 00:23:59.681
Where did you say
Tweener was headed?

390
00:23:59.705 --> 00:24:00.816
Up on the main drag.

391
00:24:00.840 --> 00:24:02.840
He's supposed to find a shovel.

392
00:24:09.248 --> 00:24:10.826
In. No.

393
00:24:10.850 --> 00:24:12.632
No. no. no. In!

394
00:24:19.091 --> 00:24:20.324
You're coming back. right?

395
00:24:20.393 --> 00:24:21.926
You're coming back?

396
00:24:21.994 --> 00:24:23.009
Yep.

397
00:24:23.078 --> 00:24:24.289
T-BAG: Hey. you guys!

398
00:24:24.313 --> 00:24:25.407
(BANGING ON TRUNK)

399
00:24:25.431 --> 00:24:27.131
Hey!

400
00:24:27.200 --> 00:24:29.533
Come on. man. I'm
boiling up in here!

401
00:24:40.947 --> 00:24:43.063
WOODY: I was on my
ATV. and I was hauling ass.

402
00:24:43.132 --> 00:24:46.099
I was right on her tail. and I
pulled out my gun and blam!

403
00:24:46.168 --> 00:24:48.835
That bitch treed herself. and I
brought her down in one shot.

404
00:24:48.904 --> 00:24:51.238
What did she weigh?
At least a hunny.

405
00:24:51.307 --> 00:24:52.439
Maybe 110.

406
00:24:52.525 --> 00:24:53.785
Come on out and
see us if you want.

407
00:24:53.809 --> 00:24:55.392
It's gonna be a good time.

408
00:24:55.444 --> 00:24:57.328
Yeah. I just might do that.

409
00:24:57.396 --> 00:24:58.396
(DOOR CLOSING)

410
00:25:04.954 --> 00:25:07.087
Hey. now. what you digging?

411
00:25:09.892 --> 00:25:12.659
Some stuff in my grandpa's yard.

412
00:25:12.728 --> 00:25:15.562
We got a bigger one in the
back if you're going deep.

413
00:25:15.630 --> 00:25:17.281
No. this will do.

414
00:25:19.735 --> 00:25:23.019
Damn it if I don't know
you from somewhere.

415
00:25:23.088 --> 00:25:24.905
Maybe I know your grandpa.

416
00:25:24.974 --> 00:25:28.070
I doubt it. man. He moved
here. like. a month ago. so...

417
00:25:28.094 --> 00:25:30.494
What's his name?

418
00:25:30.563 --> 00:25:32.879
His name's Grandpa. All right?

419
00:25:32.949 --> 00:25:34.659
Look. man. can
you just ring this up?

420
00:25:34.683 --> 00:25:36.066
I got to get out of here.

421
00:25:36.134 --> 00:25:38.769
Sure thing.
fella. I'll ring it up.

422
00:25:38.838 --> 00:25:40.454
I'll ring it right now.

423
00:25:42.941 --> 00:25:44.858
(GROANING)

424
00:25:44.927 --> 00:25:46.860
I've seen you. on TV.

425
00:25:46.928 --> 00:25:48.829
You're one of them
Fox River boys.

426
00:26:11.270 --> 00:26:13.087
You got it wrong. man.

427
00:26:13.155 --> 00:26:14.921
No. I think I got it right.

428
00:26:16.659 --> 00:26:18.158
WOODY: We're closed!

429
00:26:28.387 --> 00:26:30.420
Sorry. bud.

430
00:26:30.489 --> 00:26:32.256
We're closing up early today.

431
00:26:34.042 --> 00:26:35.525
Wait. hold on.

432
00:26:36.328 --> 00:26:37.961
Stay right there.

433
00:26:39.030 --> 00:26:40.280
(TWEENER GROANS)

434
00:26:46.638 --> 00:26:50.118
You're going down just like
your buddy. you son of a bitch.

435
00:26:53.862 --> 00:26:55.211
Where's the kid?

436
00:26:56.665 --> 00:26:58.165
Where's the kid?

437
00:26:58.233 --> 00:26:59.967
SCOFIELD: He's back here.

438
00:27:00.035 --> 00:27:01.351
LINCOLN: Get up.

439
00:27:05.441 --> 00:27:08.442
Come on. tough guy. Let's go.

440
00:27:13.699 --> 00:27:15.382
(BANGING ON TRUNK)

441
00:27:16.835 --> 00:27:18.585
(PANTING)

442
00:27:21.690 --> 00:27:22.690
(CHUCKLES)

443
00:27:27.146 --> 00:27:28.945
(GROANING)

444
00:27:34.086 --> 00:27:35.719
Where the hell are they?

445
00:27:49.568 --> 00:27:51.652
Maricruz. Baby. open up.

446
00:27:52.905 --> 00:27:54.070
Theresa!

447
00:27:54.139 --> 00:27:57.924
(SHUSHING) It's
me. It's me. okay?

448
00:27:57.993 --> 00:27:59.604
Fernando. what
are you doing here?

449
00:27:59.628 --> 00:28:01.172
(STAMMERING) You can't be here.

450
00:28:01.196 --> 00:28:02.741
I know. Theresa.
I know. I just got...

451
00:28:02.765 --> 00:28:04.581
Where's your sister? I
need to see Maricruz.

452
00:28:04.649 --> 00:28:06.427
She's getting her picture
taken with my mom and dad.

453
00:28:06.451 --> 00:28:07.691
The wedding's at 2:30.

454
00:28:07.736 --> 00:28:09.219
I need to see her now.

455
00:28:09.288 --> 00:28:10.654
You have to go.

456
00:28:10.723 --> 00:28:12.767
She's the mother
of my kid. Theresa.

457
00:28:12.791 --> 00:28:14.541
Please.

458
00:28:14.610 --> 00:28:17.410
You don't want her to marry
Hector. do you? Do you?

459
00:28:21.132 --> 00:28:23.466
I'll go see if I can go get her.

460
00:28:24.203 --> 00:28:26.043
Wait in here. Okay.

461
00:28:39.901 --> 00:28:41.935
Hey. Lance. I got
a question for you.

462
00:28:42.003 --> 00:28:43.286
Yes?

463
00:28:44.072 --> 00:28:45.755
You know who I am?

464
00:28:49.895 --> 00:28:52.546
I happened to see the
news last night. yes.

465
00:28:54.650 --> 00:28:57.517
Hey. I don't care. I've got
some skeletons in my closet. too.

466
00:28:57.586 --> 00:28:59.636
One of whom wears a dress.

467
00:29:01.023 --> 00:29:02.439
Thank you.

468
00:29:02.507 --> 00:29:04.185
I appreciate your
lack of judgment.

469
00:29:04.209 --> 00:29:06.710
From what I can tell. you
didn't do anything wrong.

470
00:29:06.778 --> 00:29:09.696
but it's none of my business.
and you don't need to talk about it.

471
00:29:09.765 --> 00:29:11.681
The whole thing just...

472
00:29:13.318 --> 00:29:14.384
(SIGHS)

473
00:29:14.453 --> 00:29:16.736
I never meant for it to happen.

474
00:29:19.341 --> 00:29:21.636
Okay. you do not need
to answer this question.

475
00:29:21.660 --> 00:29:22.676
Hmm?

476
00:29:22.745 --> 00:29:25.262
But were you and
that guy. like. uh...

477
00:29:30.185 --> 00:29:33.119
You're right. I don't
want to talk about it.

478
00:29:36.142 --> 00:29:38.609
You done? Yeah.

479
00:29:38.677 --> 00:29:42.079
Does it worry you
that he's out there?

480
00:29:42.148 --> 00:29:44.030
(KNOCKING AT DOOR)

481
00:29:45.317 --> 00:29:47.033
Give me one second.

482
00:29:56.911 --> 00:29:58.211
Dad.

483
00:29:58.280 --> 00:29:59.529
Sara. hi.

484
00:29:59.598 --> 00:30:01.481
I got your message.

485
00:30:01.550 --> 00:30:03.333
Please. come in.

486
00:30:06.555 --> 00:30:09.205
SARA: Lance. this
is my father. Frank.

487
00:30:10.109 --> 00:30:11.109
How do you do?

488
00:30:11.176 --> 00:30:12.370
SARA: Dad. this
is my friend Lance.

489
00:30:12.394 --> 00:30:14.594
Pleasure to meet
you. sir. I voted for you.

490
00:30:14.662 --> 00:30:16.880
Well. thank you.
I appreciate that.

491
00:30:16.932 --> 00:30:18.498
Sara. I can take off.

492
00:30:18.567 --> 00:30:20.350
No need.

493
00:30:20.419 --> 00:30:21.718
Only take a minute.

494
00:30:21.787 --> 00:30:23.080
How about you
step into my office.

495
00:30:23.104 --> 00:30:24.365
and you make yourself at home.

496
00:30:24.389 --> 00:30:25.522
Sure.

497
00:30:35.333 --> 00:30:36.573
SARA: So...

498
00:30:38.153 --> 00:30:42.088
So. in my program. we've been
talking a lot about making amends.

499
00:30:42.157 --> 00:30:45.308
and I've been
thinking a lot about...

500
00:30:47.179 --> 00:30:50.297
About some of the
choices I've made lately.

501
00:30:50.365 --> 00:30:52.332
and I know that
that affects you.

502
00:30:54.886 --> 00:30:55.952
And...

503
00:30:57.222 --> 00:31:00.924
And I wanted to tell
you that I'm sorry.

504
00:31:00.993 --> 00:31:03.153
You don't have
to say you're sorry.

505
00:31:03.294 --> 00:31:04.661
Yeah. I do.

506
00:31:04.729 --> 00:31:08.131
And it must be hard to
understand why I did it.

507
00:31:10.502 --> 00:31:15.355
I had no idea that I was putting
these guys back out on the street.

508
00:31:15.424 --> 00:31:19.092
I thought I was saving the
life of an innocent man and...

509
00:31:19.161 --> 00:31:21.194
And I know that you didn't read

510
00:31:21.263 --> 00:31:24.147
the information I gave you on
Lincoln Burrows but he is innocent.

511
00:31:24.216 --> 00:31:27.651
and a lot of the people
involved right now are dead.

512
00:31:31.590 --> 00:31:32.739
(SARA SIGHS)

513
00:31:34.509 --> 00:31:37.377
I'm sorry. This isn't
why I called you.

514
00:31:39.264 --> 00:31:40.497
I'm fine

515
00:31:41.833 --> 00:31:43.400
but I'm scared.

516
00:31:46.037 --> 00:31:50.574
